The paper deals with the problem of maximizing a monotone submodular function subject to a knapsack constraint, which is a well-studied problem in theoretical computer science. The paper proposes an algorithm that achieves a nearly-optimal approximation guarantee with a running time that is nearly linear in the input size. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
